 draw upon a variety of voices, spanning various religious and ethnic communities, including Hindus, Muslims, Jains, Parsees and Siddhi Africans, and caste identities, such as that of the bard, ballad singer, king, priest, court chronicler, soldier, mason and drummer.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aArt and historyzIndiazGujarat. 0aVisual anthropologyzIndiazGujarat. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  aDynastic history, elites, etnohistory, Gujarat, Halvad-Dhrangadhra, Indian kingdoms, Jhala court, Jhala dynasty, Jhalavad, Kshatriya, Kuva-no-ker, miniature paintings, Rajput, Rani Jijima, western India.1 aJhala, Angma D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJhala, Jayasinji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcClenaghan, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGrath, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLeod, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOppenheim, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez97831106498260 cEPUBz97831106056620 cprintz978311060128240uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9783110601299zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110601299/original  a978-3-11-064982-6 Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA